 of pennsylvania bs university of southern california marshall school of business mba  honorary doctorate degrees occupation founder  chairman huntsman corporation net worth us billion  spouses karen haight children  relatives jon son peter son christina daughter kathleen daughter david son paul son james son jennifer daughter mark son awards othmer gold medal  bower award from the franklin institute  armenias medal of honor  carnegie medal of philanthropy award  jon meade huntsman sr born june   is an american businessman and philanthropist he is the founder and executive chairman of huntsman corporation a global manufacturer and marketer of specialty chemicals huntsman plastics are used in a wide variety of familiar objects including formerly mcdonalds clamshell burger containers huntsman corporation also manufactures a wide variety of organic and inorganic chemicals that include polyurethanes textiles and pigments huntsmans philanthropic giving exceeds  billion focusing on areas of cancer research programs at various universities and aid to armenia contents  early life and education  business career  dolco packaging corporation  huntsman container corporation  huntsman chemical company  huntsman corporation nyse hun  huntsman gay global capital  scientific awards and honors  personal life  religion  politics  nixon administration  presidential elections   utah gubernatorial election   republican presidential nomination  philanthropy  cancer research  education  aid to armenia  awards  controversy  references  external links early life and educationedit jon meade huntsman was born in blackfoot idaho his mother sarah kathleen née robison was a homemaker and his father alonzo blaine huntsman was an educator in  the family moved to palo alto california where alonzo pursued graduate studies at stanford university earning an ma and edd he then became a superintendent of schools in the los altos california district jon huntsman attended palo alto high school where he became student body president he was recruited by harold zellerbach chairman of crownzellerbach paper company to attend the wharton school of the university of pennsylvania on a zellerbach scholarship he graduated from wharton in the spring of  a brother of the sigma chi fraternity huntsman married karen haight daughter of david b haight in june  both are members of the church of jesus christ of latterday saints or lds church in july  huntsman left to serve for two years in the us navy as a us naval gunnery officer he subsequently earned an mba from the university of southern californias marshall school of business business careeredit dolco packaging corporationedit in  huntsman was employed by olson brothers inc an eggproducing company in los angeles there he rose through the ranks to the position of vice president of operations recognizing that the company sustained substantial losses due to poor packaging huntsman became interested in developing a better alternative his leadership was key in developing the first plastic egg carton in  he established contact with the polystyrene operations of the dow chemical company in  he became president of a joint venture between olson brothers inc and dow chemical the dolco packaging corporation huntsman container corporationedit seeing an opportunity to create packaging for the emerging fastfood industry huntsman left dolco in  to form the huntsman container corporation with his brother blaine and others in fullerton california plants were constructed in fullerton california in  and in troy ohio in  since cash flow was an issue for the new company huntsman mortgaged his house and borrowed heavily from banks in  the company nearly collapsed when an arab oil embargo cut off supplies of polystyrene used to make styrofoam in  huntsman container corporation created the clamshell container for mcdonalds big mac the company also developed other popular products including the first plastic plates bowls and fastfood containers in  after completion of its first international plant at skelmersdale england a stock deal was arranged to sell huntsman container corporation to keyes fiber company huntsman continued to serve as ceo of the container business for four more years and held a directorship of keyes fiber company huntsman chemical company  huntsman corporation nyse hunedit in  after serving as an lds church of jesus christ of latter day saints mission president in washington dc for three years huntsman continued his plastics and petrochemical pursuits with the formation of a new company huntsman chemical corporation in salt lake city utah in his capacity as ceo and chairman he grew the business into a multibilliondollar company in part by acquiring a number of businesses in the polystyrene industry when they were not seen as profitable between  and  huntsman acquired  companies  of which turned out to be hugely profitable in  the huntsman chemical corporation was renamed the huntsman corporation in  peter r huntsman became president and coo of huntsman corporation in  he replaced his father as the company’s ceo jon m huntsman continued to be involved in the company as chairman during the s huntsman continued its pattern of expansion both in america and around the world and reorganization huntsman corporation became publicly traded on the new york stock exchange in  as of  huntsman reported that it operated  manufacturing and rd facilities in  countries and employed approximately  associates huntsman gay global capitaledit in  huntsman cofounded an additional new private equity firm huntsman gay global capital joining former bain capital executive robert c gay – managing director to focus on investments in middle market companies among huntsmans partners is pro football hall of fame quarterback steve young scientific awards and honorsedit huntsman has been awarded thirteen honorary doctorate degrees at various universities in  he received the othmer gold medal awarded by the chemical heritage foundation in recognition of contributions in research innovation legislation or philanthropy in  he received the leadership award for lifetime achievement from the chemical marketing and economics cme group in  he received the bower award from the franklin institute personal lifeedit huntsman has been married to his wife karen for more than  years they are the parents of  children and have  grandchildren two of whom are adopted from china and indiacitation needed on december   huntsmans son james then age  was kidnapped and held for  million ransom by nicholas hans byrd a former classmate fbi agents traced the kidnapper and rescued james unharmed but agent al jacobsen was stabbed in the chest during the arrest  huntsmans second eldest son peter r huntsman took over as ceo of the huntsman corporation from huntsman sr in  huntsmans eldest son jon huntsman jr also served as a huntsman corporation executive he was elected governor of utah in  later became ambassador to china and was a candidate in the republican party presidential primaries in  jon huntsman sr has published a book about his life experience communicating moral lessons titled winners never cheat everyday values we learned as children but may have forgotten it was published by wharton school publishing in  a second edition titled winners never cheat even in difficult times made the wall street journals bestsellers list huntsman is a fourtime cancer survivor religionedit huntsman is a member of the lds church he served as an area seventy from  to  he also served as a regional representative stake president and as president of the washington dc mission from  to  politicsedit in  he was chairman of the western states republican leaders he was also the republican party of utah national committeeman from  to  he is a friend of conservative radio talk show host glenn beck and has been interviewed on his show he is more socially conservative than his son jon huntsman jrcitation needed his focus is cancer thus he is close friends with both glenn beck on the right and harry reid on the left who have both helped further the mission of huntsman cancer institute nixon administrationedit while the huntsman container corporations first packaging plant was being built in  huntsman joined the nixon administration as associate administrator of the department of health education and welfare and later served as special assistant and staff secretary to president nixon upon completion of the second huntsman container site in troy ohio in  huntsman left the white house staff to become president and ceo of huntsman container while still serving  in a nonpaid position  as a consultant to the office of the president presidential electionsedit he served as chairman for utah in ronald reagans presidential campaign in  and george h w bushs campaigns in  and   utah gubernatorial electionedit in march  huntsman announced he would run against incumbent utah governor norm bangerter in the republican primary huntsman was leading in public opinion polls sometimes by a doubledigit margin he reportedly raised almost  in campaign advertising returning all funds raised back to the donors a few weeks later huntsman went on a day business trip to asia with his friend us senator jake garn who was chairman of governor bangerters campaign in midapril huntsman dropped out of the gubernatorial race and endorsed the governor saying that party unity and his business responsibilities were more important than his political career and asking political independents to support bangerter later that year governor bangerter appointed huntsman to be the first ambassador for economic development for the state of utah  republican presidential nominationedit huntsmans son jon m huntsman jr served in the administrations of five us presidents including barack obama and was a candidate for the  republican presidential nomination there was considerable speculation that the viability of jon huntsman jrs campaign might depend on jon huntsman srs willingness to fund advertising for it via the superpac our destiny pac jon huntsman jr reportedly downplayed the possibility of receiving campaign funding from his family before the new hampshire republican primary  telling npr that the huntsman family gives to humanitarian causes and doesnt consider a political campaign to be a humanitarian cause however reports filed with the federal election commission later showed that our destiny pac received  million in contributions  million of it from huntsman sr much of that money was spent on campaign ads including  on campaign ads in new hampshire in the two months before the january primary huntsman sr appeared on stage with jon huntsman jr and his wife and daughters at the thirdplace finish celebration in manchester new hampshire huntsman jr announced his intention in manchester to continue the campaign in south carolina but dropped out on january  in advance of the vote there throwing his support to mitt romney philanthropyedit huntsman is widely recognized for his humanitarian giving which including contributions to the homeless the ill and the underprivileged exceeds  billion and has assisted thousands both domestically and internationally the chronicle of philanthropy placed jon and karen huntsman second on their  list of largest american donors on january   the salt lake tribune included him among the  utahns who most influenced our state in the th century for his donations to education and medical research in  jon and karen huntsman were presented with the entrepreneur of the year award for principlecentered leadership in  he received the humanitarian of the year award presented by larry king of cnn in november  the american cancer society presented him its medal of honor for cancer philanthropy and in  he was awarded the william e simon prize for philanthropic leadership in  he was awarded the philanthropy roundtable’s carnegie medal of philanthropy award cancer researchedit the huntsman cancer institute at the university of utah one of huntsmans most notable causes is the huntsman cancer institute hci at the university of utah of which he is the founder and principal benefactor he and his wife karen established the huntsman cancer institute in  with a gift of  million from the huntsman family the huntsmans gave the institute a further  million in  an amount roughly equal to a years total distribution to researchers from the american cancer society their goal was to accelerate the work of curing cancer through human genetics the institute is now one of americas major cancer research centers dedicated to finding a cure for cancer with a stateoftheart cancer specialty hospital the institute continues to receive substantial gifts from the huntsman family huntsman who himself is a cancer survivor has stated except for my family and faith there is no cause more important to me than fighting cancer i have committed the rest of my life to doing all i can to support clinical and research efforts to eliminate this disease to date the huntsman family and close associates have donated more than  million in support of the mission of hci in november  huntsman donated or raised  million to huntsman cancer institute at the university of utah for the construction of a new research building dedicated to childrens cancer construction of the primary childrens and families cancer research center at huntsman cancer institute is nearing completion and will be dedicated june   on huntsmans th birthday huntsman has also promoted support of the institute through the sigma chi fraternity sigma chi chose the huntsman cancer foundation as one of its preferred philanthropic partners in december  as of april   sigma chi had raised their first onemillion dollars for cancer research by  sigma chis total has reached over five million dollars for cancer research educationedit jon m huntsman center at the university of utah in salt lake city jon m huntsman hall at the wharton school of the university of pennsylvania huntsman has supported the university of utah in salt lake city in other ways as well the seat jon m huntsman center for special events opened in  and is used for gymnastics basketball and volleyball it has been the site of national championships in both gymnastics and basketball including ncaa mens basketball as of  the huntsmans have supported the building of an additional basketball practice facility to be named the jon m and karen huntsman basketball center huntsman has also given support to other universities he has served as chairman of the board of overseers of his alma mater the wharton school of the university of pennsylvania in philadelphia pa one of the schools signature buildings jon huntsman hall was named in his honor huntsman made an unrestricted gift of more than  million to wharton which was critical to development of the  million project as of  the huntsmans also endowed the huntsman program in international studies and business at the university of pennsylvania a fouryear undergraduate program that combines business education and liberal arts in  huntsman gave  million to utah state university in logan utah for the huntsman environmental research center at a press conference to announce the gift huntsman said the preservation of the environment is the single most important issue in the world the huntsmans also donated  to rebuild the alumni center renamed the david b haight alumni center in honor of mrs huntsmans father in december  utah state university announced that its college of business would be renamed the jon m huntsman school of business in recognition of a gift from huntsman and his wife of  million a major contributor for the new  million school of business building referred to as huntsman hall—the largest in the universitys history to that time in  huntsman and charles koch donated another  million to the huntsman school of business for student scholarships and a new center for growth and opportunity the law library at brigham young university built in  was expanded and renamed for howard w hunter in  with financial support from jon and karen huntsman and other donors a new library building at southern utah university named in honor of retiring suu president gerald r sherratt contains the jon and karen huntsman reading room the huntsmans also contributed to the karen h huntsman library in snow college utah completed in  it is a green building expected to be the first academic library in the state to achieve gold leadership in energy and environmental design certification aid to armeniaedit huntsman has also contributed to efforts to rebuild in armenia which was devastated by an earthquake in  he and other family members have made  trips to armenia over  years he estimates that he has given at least  million to relief efforts in armenia including money to build schools and hospitals one of his earliest projects there involved setting up a plant to make prestressed concrete to supply building materials for reconstruction and to employ armenians the huntsmans have built a tile roofing plant in yerevan apartment complexes and a k school in the city of gyumri the huntsmans also provide scholarships to bring armenian students to american to study at utah state university huntsman has been granted citizenship in the country and awarded two medals of honor by armenia one of them the st mesrop mashtots order huntsmans donations of more than  billion overall dropped him from the forbes  list as of  his current wealth is not disclosed however he was listed as number  on the forbes worlds richest persons for  he is one of only  of the worlds  billionaires to have donated more than  billion he has said that he wants to die broke by giving his money away to various charities rocky anderson democratic mayor of salt lake city has said of huntsman i was impressed with jon from the first when he told me he lost respect for richard nixon when he learned that nixon had not given anything to charity one year he was president  it was clear to me that jons real motivation in his work and accumulation of wealth was to give much of what he has to make peoples lives better awardsedit   studentbody president palo alto high school   awarded the crown zellerbach scholarship to the wharton school university of pennsylvania   university of pennsylvania student alumni award of merit undergrad   university of pennsylvania spoon award most outstanding student graduate   international balfour award most outstanding sigma chi in uscanada   josé marti brotherhood award from cuban americans most respected us citizen   armenian medal of honor   american academy of achievement   kaveler award most outstanding ceo chemical industry   great humanitarian award freedom foundation   national caring award caring institute   horatio alger national award   armenian presidential award   university of pennsylvania alumni award of merit   named one of ten most influential utahns in the th century   entrepreneur of the year ernst  young   humanitarian of the year   othmer award outstanding inventions in plastics chemical heritage foundation   giant in our city award salt lake chamber of commerce   american red cross excellence in governance award   medal of honor american cancer society   trustee emeritus university of pennsylvania   chairman emeritus the wharton school board of overseers university of pennsylvania   distinguished public service award american assn for cancer research   inducted into idaho’s hall of fame   national award for charity restoring honor day washington dc   service above self award   wsj’s innovator of the year award   leadership award for lifetime achievement american chemical society   william e simon award for philanthropy   the franklin institute of philadelphia’s business leadership award bower award   philanthropy roundtable’s carnegie medal of philanthropy award   insider magazine listed huntsman as second largest contributor to charities in america fortune magazine names huntsman as nd most generous man in america controversyedit huntsman contributed to the resignation of the ceo of university of utah healthcare hci dr vivian lee after threatening to withhold  million in donations to the huntsman cancer institute and attacking lees character in the public sphere lee resigned after the public backlash she received particularly from editorials printed in the salt lake tribune a newspaper owned by the huntsman family in an editorial huntsman described lee as attempting a powergrab while huntsman was attempting to sever hci and university of utah ties this controversy has raised the question of how much private donors should have a say in publicly funded healthcare  referencesedit  httpswwwforbescomforbesahtml  a b huntsman chemical corporation history international directory of company histories retrieved  march    huntsman corporation new york times retrieved  march    death a blaine huntsman sr deseret news  june  retrieved  march    a b c levenich christopher summer  the fearless philanthropist philanthropy retrieved  august    gelles jeff  may  wharton receives  million in thanks jon m huntsman a former scholarship student shows gratitude to penns business school philadelphia inquirer retrieved  march    a b c mileposts huntsman corporation through the years saltlake  aug  retrieved  march    a b c d history in the s huntsman retrieved  march    a b easton nina  june  the huntsmans inside an american dynasty cnn money retrieved  march    history in the s huntsman retrieved  march    a b petrochemical heritage award chemical heritage foundation retrieved  march    history in the s huntsman retrieved  march    huntsman corporation prospectus registration file no  nasdaq  february  retrieved  march    huntsman announces details of  annual meeting of stockholders and  investor day huntsman international news release february   retrieved  march    a b primack dan  april  exclusive bob gay leaving huntsman gay cnn